I can't write when you're mad at me.

807
00:56:32,916 --> 00:56:34,582
You influence me,

808
00:56:34,749 --> 00:56:37,332
because of you, I've changed my ending.

809
00:56:37,499 --> 00:56:39,707
No suicide. The hero decides to live.

810
00:56:39,874 --> 00:56:43,707
You're right. Why incite others
to despair while you yourself

811
00:56:43,874 --> 00:56:45,290
enjoy life?

812
00:56:45,458 --> 00:56:47,665
It's hypocritical.

813
00:56:47,833 --> 00:56:50,790
Right. I wish you'd stop being so hostile.

814
00:56:51,041 --> 00:56:53,457
But I feel hostile towards you !

815
00:56:53,624 --> 00:56:54,998
About our vacation. . .

816
00:56:55,166 --> 00:56:59,582
Sorry, I've made other plans.
I'm going away by myself.

817
00:57:00,583 --> 00:57:03,123
- Where to?
- 2000 miles from Paris.

818
00:57:03,708 --> 00:57:06,582
Open up.
I lost an important document in your place.

819
00:57:06,749 --> 00:57:08,540
It might convince you.

820
00:57:08,749 --> 00:57:09,873
Convince me of what?

821
00:57:10,041 --> 00:57:11,290
Of my good faith.

822
00:57:11,458 --> 00:57:12,832
Wait there.

823
00:57:16,874 --> 00:57:19,290
Look. Take your letters back.

824
00:57:20,291 --> 00:57:22,790
I've got no use for that pack of lies.

825
00:57:36,208 --> 00:57:37,707
"Sabine, my love,

826
00:57:37,958 --> 00:57:40,707
"I hurried home to write to you.

827
00:57:40,874 --> 00:57:43,332
"I can't even go to the movies without you.

828
00:57:43,499 --> 00:57:46,957
"I left you an hour ago. It seems a lifetime.

829
00:57:47,124 --> 00:57:50,582
"We just met and you're leaving."

830
00:57:50,749 --> 00:57:52,998
I'll be back in three days.

831
00:57:53,249 --> 00:57:56,332
Will you be faithful to me?

832
00:57:56,499 --> 00:58:00,415
Of course I will !

833
00:58:01,374 --> 00:58:02,915
What about you?

834
00:58:03,083 --> 00:58:06,415
I have no choice. I'm totally

835
00:58:06,791 --> 00:58:09,623
under your spell, you bastard.

836
00:58:09,791 --> 00:58:11,873
Good. Stay that way.

837
00:58:12,041 --> 00:58:15,707
But you said you weren't jealous
and I was free.

838
00:58:15,874 --> 00:58:18,373
I don't plan to. I just want to know.

839
00:58:18,541 --> 00:58:21,915
True, I'm not jealous. Do as you please.

840
00:58:22,124 --> 00:58:24,623
But try and be faithful to me,

841
00:58:25,124 --> 00:58:26,582
at least in your head.

842
00:58:27,999 --> 00:58:29,248
Let's shake on it.

843
00:58:29,583 --> 00:58:31,748
It's a deal.

844
00:58:31,916 --> 00:58:34,082
First to fail is a worm !

845
00:58:47,166 --> 00:58:48,457
Here are the galleys.

846
00:58:48,624 --> 00:58:52,373
The book spells out everything
General de Gaulle did

847
00:58:52,541 --> 00:58:56,165
on May 30, 1 968, when
he disappeared for a whole day.

848
00:58:56,541 --> 00:58:59,290
The press is dying to get hold of this book.

849
00:58:59,458 --> 00:59:01,540
The boss says it's top secret.

850
00:59:01,624 --> 00:59:02,623
Really?

851
00:59:02,708 --> 00:59:06,082
Yes, there's only one set of proofs,

852
00:59:06,208 --> 00:59:09,165
and the type will be destroyed right
after printing.

853
00:59:09,333 --> 00:59:12,832
Keep it in the safe. I'm off.

854
00:59:12,999 --> 00:59:15,748
Don't tell me the combination !

855
01:00:54,083 --> 01:00:56,665
She was hurt by
the misunderstandings between you.

856
01:00:57,708 --> 01:00:59,623
Nobody understood her.

857
01:00:59,791 --> 01:01:02,623
People assumed she was bitter.
That wasn't it.

858
01:01:02,833 --> 01:01:05,915
She just couldn't stand hypocrisy.

859
01:01:06,083 --> 01:01:07,582
So she was sore at everybody:

860
01:01:07,749 --> 01:01:11,457
the press, clergy, shopkeepers, politicians.

861
01:01:11,708 --> 01:01:14,207
Did you know that, at heart,

862
01:01:14,374 --> 01:01:16,665
your mother was an anarchist?

863
01:01:16,833 --> 01:01:18,415
Maybe so.

864
01:01:18,583 --> 01:01:21,748
I never thought of my mother as an anarchist.

865
01:01:22,583 --> 01:01:25,207
Of course, with me, she wasn't like that.

866
01:01:26,083 --> 01:01:28,290
She was like a little bird.

867
01:01:31,124 --> 01:01:32,290
A little bird.

868
01:01:32,458 --> 01:01:36,123
After your father's death,

869
01:01:36,291 --> 01:01:39,748
he and I were always good friends,

870
01:01:39,916 --> 01:01:43,998
her eyesight began to fail,
but she wouldn't wear glasses.

871
01:01:44,833 --> 01:01:47,332
But we managed anyway.

872
01:01:47,499 --> 01:01:49,707
I'd read out loud to her.

873
01:01:49,874 --> 01:01:51,498
One hour every night,

874
01:01:51,874 --> 01:01:53,582
sometimes two hours.

875
01:01:55,666 --> 01:01:56,873
You still like books?

876
01:01:57,666 --> 01:01:59,582
Yes, I do, Mr Lucien.

877
01:01:59,749 --> 01:02:00,832
When you were a kid,

878
01:02:00,999 --> 01:02:03,665
you were always buried in a book.

879
01:02:05,999 --> 01:02:07,915
Remember the first time we met?

880
01:02:08,249 --> 01:02:10,748
At the Edith Piaf concert.

881
01:02:14,333 --> 01:02:17,832
But we'd seen each other before that.

882
01:02:25,166 --> 01:02:28,790
lmagine her shock seeing you in the street

883
01:02:28,958 --> 01:02:31,540
when you were supposed to be in school.

884
01:02:31,708 --> 01:02:34,665
I didn't know you. I asked her,

885
01:02:34,833 --> 01:02:36,332
"Which one's your son?"

886
01:02:39,666 --> 01:02:41,623
You seemed much taller.

887
01:02:41,791 --> 01:02:43,332
That's because you were so small.

888
01:02:54,041 --> 01:02:55,415
Here you are!

889
01:02:56,333 --> 01:02:59,207
The extra homework made you sick

890
01:02:59,458 --> 01:03:01,207
and your parents fell for it.

891
01:03:01,374 --> 01:03:04,207
What pretext did you wangle
from them this time?

892
01:03:04,749 --> 01:03:06,248
Let's see their note.

893
01:03:06,458 --> 01:03:08,040
- I haven't any.
- Is that so?

894
01:03:08,666 --> 01:03:11,707
You won't get away with it. Not this time!

895
01:03:13,499 --> 01:03:15,790
It's my mother, Sir.

896
01:03:15,958 --> 01:03:17,665
What about your mother?

897
01:03:17,833 --> 01:03:19,498
She just died.

898
01:03:22,083 --> 01:03:25,040
I'm sorry, son. I didn't know.

899
01:03:28,541 --> 01:03:29,623
Doinel !

900
01:03:30,916 --> 01:03:32,332
Excuse me, son.

901
01:03:32,499 --> 01:03:33,790
Simonot!

902
01:03:34,374 --> 01:03:45,040
The Hare.

903
01:03:45,166 --> 01:03:49,040
By Jean Richepin.

904
01:03:50,916 --> 01:03:52,415
Sit down, boys.

905
01:04:18,833 --> 01:04:21,290
Just wait till I get you home!

906
01:04:22,624 --> 01:04:24,123
To tell you the truth,

907
01:04:25,541 --> 01:04:28,165
I felt bad that you missed her funeral.

908
01:04:28,333 --> 01:04:30,165
I couldn't help it.

909
01:04:31,083 --> 01:04:34,082
I was in an army jail in Germany.

910
01:04:34,249 --> 01:04:35,957
The C.O. sent for me.

911
01:04:36,124 --> 01:04:39,665
He gave me three days off for the funeral,

912
01:04:39,833 --> 01:04:41,457
but he couldn't issue my travel order.

913
01:04:41,624 --> 01:04:44,498
I couldn't afford a ticket, so I stayed in jail.

914
01:04:45,166 --> 01:04:47,290
I was puzzled by your absence,

915
01:04:47,833 --> 01:04:50,832
but I felt sure it wasn't indifference.

916
01:04:50,999 --> 01:04:53,040
Your mother loved you.

917
01:04:53,208 --> 01:04:56,373
In a strange way, perhaps,
but she really cared.

918
01:05:00,624 --> 01:05:03,873
It wasn't easy to get a plot
in Montmartre cemetery.

919
01:05:04,041 --> 01:05:06,373
But I insisted.

920
01:05:07,124 --> 01:05:09,207
She loved that area.

921
01:05:09,749 --> 01:05:13,248
She's buried right next
to Marguerite Gautier.

922
01:05:14,416 --> 01:05:16,123
You know who she was?

923
01:05:17,624 --> 01:05:19,040
I don't think so.

924
01:05:19,208 --> 01:05:23,665
The heroine of CamiIIe,
by Alexandre Dumas.

925
01:05:23,833 --> 01:05:25,832
I thought he'd invented her.

926
01:05:25,999 --> 01:05:27,873
No, she really existed.

927
01:05:28,624 --> 01:05:31,832
Your mother's buried next to her.
Didn't you notice?

928
01:05:32,916 --> 01:05:36,165
Frankly, I've never visited my mother's grave.

929
01:05:36,333 --> 01:05:40,582
I didn't even know where she was buried.

930
01:05:41,791 --> 01:05:45,207
I can hardly believe my ears!

931
01:05:48,166 --> 01:05:49,623
Know what?

932
01:05:49,833 --> 01:05:51,665
When do you report back to work?

933
01:05:51,833 --> 01:05:55,290
At 2:30 p.m.

934
01:05:55,458 --> 01:05:58,790
It's 1 9 francs. That's 9.50 each.

935
01:06:04,499 --> 01:06:06,623
After your mother's death

936
01:06:06,791 --> 01:06:09,457
I sort of broke down.

937
01:06:13,624 --> 01:06:15,915
So I quit my Civil Service job.

938
01:06:16,416 --> 01:06:20,165
I was fed up with bowing and scraping.

939
01:06:22,291 --> 01:06:25,332
Then, I set up a small business on my own.

940
01:06:28,166 --> 01:06:29,707
Very small.

941
01:06:30,374 --> 01:06:33,415
I rent dress clothes by the day.

942
01:06:36,916 --> 01:06:38,707
The grave's this way.

943
01:06:51,374 --> 01:06:53,707
By now, you surely realise that

944
01:06:53,999 --> 01:06:56,832
your parents can't be blamed
for all your troubles.

945
01:06:57,458 --> 01:07:00,082
Some were your fault as well.

946
01:07:03,874 --> 01:07:06,207
I'd like to see you again.

947
01:07:08,166 --> 01:07:11,207
You may not believe this,

948
01:07:12,291 --> 01:07:13,832
but the more I look at you,

949
01:07:16,166 --> 01:07:18,290
the more you remind me of her.

950
01:07:23,374 --> 01:07:25,457
How sad it all is!

951
01:07:25,624 --> 01:07:29,290
Anyway, I'm glad you've finally
seen your mother's grave.

952
01:07:29,708 --> 01:07:31,998
By the way,

953
01:07:32,749 --> 01:07:34,707
here's my card.

954
01:07:35,291 --> 01:07:39,123
If you ever need a tuxedo,

955
01:07:39,916 --> 01:07:43,832
you're a size 36. For you, it's free!

956
01:07:44,666 --> 01:07:47,915
Thanks, Mr Lucien. If I ever need one. . .

957
01:07:56,499 --> 01:07:58,415
May I kiss you?

958
01:08:02,874 --> 01:08:04,123
"My darling Sabine,

959
01:08:04,916 --> 01:08:07,040
"whom I love and who shuns me.

960
01:08:07,208 --> 01:08:11,373
"I must tell you my strange meeting today.

961
01:08:12,458 --> 01:08:14,123
"I saw Mr Lucien.

962
01:08:14,291 --> 01:08:17,165
"He was one of my mother's lovers,

963
01:08:17,333 --> 01:08:18,373
"the main one.

964
01:08:19,083 --> 01:08:21,998
"His questions
about my mother reminded me

965
01:08:22,166 --> 01:08:25,165
"of the psychologist. In there, we called her

966
01:08:25,333 --> 01:08:26,582
"the spychologist."

967
01:08:31,999 --> 01:08:33,582
Your parents say you're a liar.

968
01:08:35,833 --> 01:08:38,123
Well, I lie sometimes,

969
01:08:38,749 --> 01:08:43,748
because if I told the truth,
they wouldn't believe me. So I lie.

970
01:08:44,416 --> 01:08:47,290
"Mr Lucien said my mother
was like a little bird."

971
01:08:48,583 --> 01:08:50,082
A little bird !

972
01:08:51,124 --> 01:08:53,665
"Were we talking about the same person?

973
01:08:54,666 --> 01:08:58,665
"Still, she taught me that love
is the only thing that matters.

974
01:09:00,333 --> 01:09:02,665
"When she came home,
I'd pretend to be asleep.

975
01:09:16,708 --> 01:09:18,373
"Love's the antithesis of prison.

976
01:09:18,749 --> 01:09:22,707
"I was only 1 3, but the spychologist
wanted to know about my love life."

977
01:09:24,291 --> 01:09:26,498
Have you ever slept with a girl?

978
01:09:31,541 --> 01:09:35,832
No, but some guys told me
where to go if I felt like it.

979
01:09:35,999 --> 01:09:38,998
They said the girl hung around Saint-Denis.

980
01:09:39,166 --> 01:09:41,123
So I went there and. . .

981
01:09:41,958 --> 01:09:44,165
The girls bawled me out.

982
01:09:44,333 --> 01:09:46,540
So I got scared and beat it.

983
01:09:46,749 --> 01:09:48,873
I went back there a few times.

984
01:09:49,041 --> 01:09:52,582
Once, a man asked what I was doing.

985
01:09:52,916 --> 01:09:56,873
He was North African.
I told him because he knew the girls.

986
01:09:57,041 --> 01:09:59,582
He said he knew one. . .

987
01:10:01,041 --> 01:10:05,207
a young one who went with guys my age.

988
01:10:06,208 --> 01:10:09,748
So he took me to her hotel.

989
01:10:09,916 --> 01:10:12,457
But she wasn't there that day.

990
01:10:12,708 --> 01:10:16,332
We waited for over two hours and then I split.

991
01:10:17,249 --> 01:10:19,457
"I started late with girls.

992
01:10:20,124 --> 01:10:24,123
"Then it was as if I wanted
to make up for lost time.

993
01:10:24,541 --> 01:10:26,665
"I needed constant reassurance.

994
01:10:27,166 --> 01:10:29,123
"Would this wide-eyed girl like me?

995
01:10:29,291 --> 01:10:31,457
"The student? The salesgirl?

996
01:10:31,624 --> 01:10:33,582
"The typist at the Ministry?

997
01:10:33,916 --> 01:10:35,665
"The night clerk's daughter?

998
01:10:36,791 --> 01:10:37,832
"One fine day..."

999
01:10:38,124 --> 01:10:39,373
A fine day, indeed.

1000
01:10:39,833 --> 01:10:40,873
"I met you, Sabine,

1001
01:10:41,291 --> 01:10:43,207
"and stopped looking at other women.

1002
01:10:43,624 --> 01:10:45,998
"Remember our first date at the movies?

1003
01:10:46,333 --> 01:10:49,665
"You clung to me because of the violence."

1004
01:10:49,833 --> 01:10:52,498
It's horrible. I hate boxing !

1005
01:11:02,791 --> 01:11:05,123
"I was so glad you hated boxing !

1006
01:11:11,916 --> 01:11:15,040
"But now you're rejecting me.

1007
01:11:15,208 --> 01:11:16,415
"I feel hopeless.

1008
01:11:16,916 --> 01:11:19,290
"I may kill off the hero of my novel."

1009
01:11:34,666 --> 01:11:37,915
Wait. If they're not legally married,

1010
01:11:38,249 --> 01:11:41,332
he can't be the kid's stepfather.

1011
01:11:41,499 --> 01:11:43,457
The boy was actually his own son,

1012
01:11:43,624 --> 01:11:46,582
but he claimed his wife's lover
was the father.

1013
01:11:46,749 --> 01:11:49,082
His defence is based on that?

1014
01:11:49,249 --> 01:11:52,415
At the moment,
he's not concerned with his defence.

1015
01:11:53,291 --> 01:11:54,790
When the mob saw him

1016
01:11:54,958 --> 01:11:57,790
spit on the kid's body, they went wild.

1017
01:11:57,958 --> 01:12:01,457
Despite the police, they almost lynched him.

1018
01:12:01,624 --> 01:12:03,415
He doesn't want a lawyer.

1019
01:12:03,583 --> 01:12:07,123
I was appointed by the Court,
but it's hopeless.

1020
01:12:07,291 --> 01:12:09,540
All he does is curse me.

1021
01:12:09,749 --> 01:12:11,790
That's why we felt that. . .

1022
01:12:11,958 --> 01:12:15,248
Don't tell me.
You felt a woman might tame the brute.

1023
01:12:15,416 --> 01:12:18,790
You know how the public feels
about child murderers.

1024
01:12:19,208 --> 01:12:21,665
Why should I feel any different?

1025
01:12:23,208 --> 01:12:25,748
Even so, I'm willing to meet him.

1026
01:12:25,958 --> 01:12:28,748
But first, I have to examine the evidence.

1027
01:12:45,999 --> 01:12:48,165
You might as well go home.

1028
01:12:48,333 --> 01:12:51,457
He just tried to kill himself.

1029
01:12:51,666 --> 01:12:54,623
An hour ago. He's in the prison infirmary.

1030
01:12:55,416 --> 01:12:57,332
- Slit his wrists.
- A piece of glass.

1031
01:12:57,499 --> 01:12:58,998
From his watch?

1032
01:12:59,999 --> 01:13:02,540
He broke the light bulb in his cell.

1033
01:13:04,083 --> 01:13:07,332
You have a week to make up your mind.

1034
01:13:07,833 --> 01:13:10,873
We'll be in touch with you.

1035
01:13:14,124 --> 01:13:17,082
I shouldn't admit it, but I'm relieved.

1036
01:13:17,749 --> 01:13:19,748
I need time to think.

1037
01:13:19,916 --> 01:13:21,957
Shall we take you to the station?

1038
01:13:22,749 --> 01:13:25,207
I'd appreciate it. I'm really upset.

1039
01:13:25,374 --> 01:13:28,665
I want a friend to meet me in Paris.
May I call him?

1040
01:13:47,416 --> 01:13:49,415
BARNERlAS
BOOKSTORE

1041
01:14:06,333 --> 01:14:09,373
Barnerias. . . Sabine Barnerias!

1042
01:14:12,624 --> 01:14:14,373
That does it!

1043
01:14:15,958 --> 01:14:19,207
I thought these things only
happened in soap operas!

1044
01:14:20,958 --> 01:14:24,998
A married man passing himself off
as a bachelor!

1045
01:15:19,249 --> 01:15:20,957
I've almost broken off with him.

1046
01:15:22,291 --> 01:15:24,873
It may be the dumbest thing I ever did.

1047
01:15:29,666 --> 01:15:31,207
And you?

1048
01:15:31,624 --> 01:15:32,957
Me?

1049
01:15:35,124 --> 01:15:36,790
The same as usual.

1050
01:15:37,999 --> 01:15:39,540
It's a deadlock.

1051
01:15:42,791 --> 01:15:44,498
I'm stumped.

1052
01:15:47,249 --> 01:15:50,748
We're both alike.
We'll probably wind up together.

1053
01:16:07,208 --> 01:16:09,498
I don't get this movie.

1054
01:16:09,666 --> 01:16:12,623
I thought he was the killer.

1055
01:16:15,166 --> 01:16:17,165
Have you got a handkerchief?

1056
01:16:18,916 --> 01:16:20,207
Only Kleenex. Want one?

1057
01:16:20,583 --> 01:16:22,665
I never blow my nose in paper.

1058
01:16:30,708 --> 01:16:31,915
Is Mr Xavier in?

1059
01:16:32,083 --> 01:16:34,082
No, he isn't.

1060
01:16:34,249 --> 01:16:36,457
Fine, I don't give a damn !

1061
01:16:49,541 --> 01:16:51,873
I must reach him immediately.

1062
01:16:52,041 --> 01:16:54,373
Give me his wife's number.

1063
01:16:54,541 --> 01:16:56,540
He's not married.

1064
01:16:56,749 --> 01:16:58,832
Then, his ex-wife's number.

1065
01:16:58,999 --> 01:17:02,582
I assure you he's never been married.

1066
01:17:04,541 --> 01:17:06,123
He hasn't?

1067
01:17:08,124 --> 01:17:10,415
Who's this? His fairy godmother?

1068
01:17:10,583 --> 01:17:13,540
That's his sister, Sabine.
Don't you know her?

1069
01:17:13,708 --> 01:17:16,998
She works in a record shop.

1070
01:17:55,458 --> 01:17:56,457
Me?

1071
01:17:56,541 --> 01:17:57,873
Yes, you.

1072
01:17:59,124 --> 01:18:02,123
Are you Sabine Barnerias?

1073
01:18:02,291 --> 01:18:03,748
No, I'm not.

1074
01:18:03,916 --> 01:18:04,957
Sorry.

1075
01:18:05,041 --> 01:18:06,915
I'm not Sabine Barnerias.

1076
01:18:07,083 --> 01:18:09,748
But you and I belong to the same sorority.

1077
01:18:09,916 --> 01:18:13,373
We're both ex-girlfriends of Antoine Doinel.

1078
01:18:14,458 --> 01:18:18,248
I saw you the other day
at the Divorce Court. I'm a lawyer.

1079
01:18:18,458 --> 01:18:21,707
I'm also Colette,
the girl from the Youth Concerts.

1080
01:18:21,874 --> 01:18:23,290
Oh, of course!

1081
01:18:24,541 --> 01:18:25,665
Going to Sabine's?

1082
01:18:25,749 --> 01:18:26,748
Yes, I am.

1083
01:18:26,833 --> 01:18:30,832
I rang. She's not home.
I don't know what to do.

1084
01:18:31,249 --> 01:18:33,498
Let's wait for her together.
Somewhere more comfortable.

1085
01:18:33,666 --> 01:18:35,665
Sure, there are benches in the courtyard.

1086
01:18:44,124 --> 01:18:47,540
I suspect you're here on a special mission.

1087
01:18:47,833 --> 01:18:49,748
Quite right. And you?

1088
01:18:49,958 --> 01:18:52,457
Me too, but it's for myself.

1089
01:18:52,624 --> 01:18:56,457
I know her brother.
I was tying up some loose ends.

1090
01:18:57,041 --> 01:18:59,498
I just read Antoine's book.
To you, it's ancient history,

1091
01:18:59,666 --> 01:19:01,623
but it shook me up.

1092
01:19:01,791 --> 01:19:03,082
Shall we sit down?

1093
01:19:07,333 --> 01:19:10,832
That heel ! He makes me
feel guilty retroactively.

1094
01:19:11,083 --> 01:19:13,415
So I'm trying to help him out.

1095
01:19:13,583 --> 01:19:17,707
I've always suspected he married me
only because you turned him down.

1096
01:19:18,374 --> 01:19:21,082
It wasn't that way at all.

1097
01:19:21,249 --> 01:19:23,123
When I met him, I was a student.

1098
01:19:23,291 --> 01:19:27,457
He had a job but we were both
too young to think of marriage.

1099
01:19:31,541 --> 01:19:33,415
Sit down. Have you eaten yet?

1100
01:19:34,083 --> 01:19:35,082
You have?

1101
01:19:35,166 --> 01:19:36,332
I ate, thanks.

1102
01:19:36,416 --> 01:19:37,665
Are you sure?

1103
01:19:38,083 --> 01:19:40,373
I can whip up an omelette.

1104
01:19:40,541 --> 01:19:43,165
No thanks, I'll just have a tangerine.

1105
01:19:44,708 --> 01:19:46,582
You want a plate for the peels?

1106
01:19:46,749 --> 01:19:49,082
Don't bother. I'll use yours.

1107
01:19:51,708 --> 01:19:52,707
Not again !

1108
01:19:52,791 --> 01:19:54,498
- Who is it?
- I don't know.

1109
01:19:54,666 --> 01:19:56,540
It's a real parade today.

1110
01:20:01,458 --> 01:20:04,248
Hello. Come in.

1111
01:20:06,791 --> 01:20:08,832
Antoine had won my parent's affection.

1112
01:20:09,249 --> 01:20:10,832
He came by often.

1113
01:20:10,958 --> 01:20:14,623
He didn't realise that now
I regarded him as a kid cousin.

1114
01:20:15,291 --> 01:20:16,332
I longed for

1115
01:20:16,416 --> 01:20:18,415
more thrilling adventures.

1116
01:20:18,583 --> 01:20:21,415
This is Albert. I've told you about him.

1117
01:20:23,041 --> 01:20:24,790
My stepfather.

1118
01:20:26,041 --> 01:20:27,290
Antoine. . .

1119
01:20:27,458 --> 01:20:28,915
I believe you've already met.

1120
01:20:29,083 --> 01:20:31,873
- We met once.
- I'll get my coat.

1121
01:20:33,208 --> 01:20:34,623
Got a cigarette?

1122
01:20:39,958 --> 01:20:43,415
I'm ready. Let's go.

1123
01:20:43,583 --> 01:20:44,915
Good night.

1124
01:20:46,083 --> 01:20:48,707
Antoine also longed for thrills.

1125
01:20:48,874 --> 01:20:51,998
Liliane and I had become close friends.

1126
01:20:52,166 --> 01:20:54,248
She spent a summer with us.

1127
01:20:54,416 --> 01:20:57,123
Antoine argued with her constantly.

1128
01:20:57,791 --> 01:21:01,457
I'm not excited, I'm calm.

1129
01:21:03,749 --> 01:21:07,165
I always have anxieties. So what?

1130
01:21:14,124 --> 01:21:16,082
Stop fighting ! Lunch is ready.

1131
01:21:18,083 --> 01:21:19,957
One day, I ran short of cash while shopping,

1132
01:21:20,124 --> 01:21:23,540
so I came home early. The door was shut.

1133
01:21:23,708 --> 01:21:25,832
Another fight, I said to myself.

1134
01:21:25,999 --> 01:21:30,915
The day before, I'd asked Antoine
to be nicer to Liliane.

1135
01:21:39,249 --> 01:21:40,415
It was a shock.

1136
01:21:40,583 --> 01:21:42,457
An even bigger one for them !

1137
01:21:42,624 --> 01:21:46,665
Antoine's justification was typical of him.

1138
01:21:46,958 --> 01:21:48,665
He'd given her a book.

1139
01:21:48,833 --> 01:21:50,790
He noticed that to protect it

1140
01:21:51,458 --> 01:21:55,082
she'd made a dust-jacket
with a newspaper. This so moved him.

1141
01:21:55,249 --> 01:21:57,123
That he hopped into bed with her!

1142
01:21:57,291 --> 01:21:59,957
- Right!
- That's perfectly logical !

1143
01:22:01,624 --> 01:22:03,665
Strangely enough, I wasn't upset.

1144
01:22:03,833 --> 01:22:08,207
My lack of jealousy made me realise
I was no longer in love with him.

1145
01:22:08,666 --> 01:22:12,332
I'd married too young.
I wasn't yet an adult. We separated.

1146
01:22:12,666 --> 01:22:15,915
He lived with Liliane
until she decided to leave him.

1147
01:22:16,499 --> 01:22:19,123
Then too, he asked me to talk her out of it.

1148
01:22:19,291 --> 01:22:21,082
Don't leave him.

1149
01:22:21,249 --> 01:22:22,707
He'll fall apart.

1150
01:22:22,874 --> 01:22:24,832
He's always falling apart.

1151
01:22:24,999 --> 01:22:29,123
He needs a wife, a mistress,
a kid sister and a wet-nurse.

1152
01:22:29,291 --> 01:22:32,040
I can't fill all those functions.

1153
01:22:32,291 --> 01:22:34,290
You're being unfair to him.

1154
01:22:34,458 --> 01:22:38,373
I can't help it. He wants everyone
to pay for his unhappy childhood.

1155
01:22:38,583 --> 01:22:41,832
Liliane really wanted to live alone
and adopt a child.

1156
01:22:42,333 --> 01:22:43,623
Which reminds me,

1157
01:22:43,791 --> 01:22:45,248
Antoine said he met you

1158
01:22:45,416 --> 01:22:47,082
one day with your baby.

1159
01:22:48,416 --> 01:22:50,248
I must kiss you.

1160
01:22:51,208 --> 01:22:53,248
Albert, you remember Antoine.

1161
01:22:53,874 --> 01:22:55,290
Albert, my husband.

1162
01:22:55,458 --> 01:22:56,832
What are you doing here?

1163
01:22:56,999 --> 01:22:58,332
Waiting for a friend.

1164
01:22:59,791 --> 01:23:02,290
You're wondering if it's a boy or a girl.

1165
01:23:03,708 --> 01:23:06,540
You must come over some evening.

1166
01:23:07,708 --> 01:23:09,957
Do you have my number?

1167
01:23:10,374 --> 01:23:11,540
I think so.

1168
01:23:11,708 --> 01:23:14,248
Well, you haven't used it lately.

1169
01:23:14,791 --> 01:23:17,623
You never used to be afraid of the phone.

1170
01:23:18,749 --> 01:23:20,748
See you soon.

1171
01:23:21,583 --> 01:23:23,790
Is your child a girl or a boy?

1172
01:23:24,291 --> 01:23:26,748
She was a little girl, Julie.

1173
01:23:27,791 --> 01:23:30,332
She's not with me because she's dead.

1174
01:23:31,374 --> 01:23:33,790
She was run over by a car.

1175
01:23:33,958 --> 01:23:35,248
Mother!

1176
01:23:52,958 --> 01:23:55,082
I didn't want any more children.

1177
01:23:55,249 --> 01:23:58,707
I didn't dare. I went back
to school. I did my best.

1178
01:23:59,374 --> 01:24:02,332
But for my husband and me, it was over.

1179
01:24:02,499 --> 01:24:03,540
We split up.

1180
01:24:05,124 --> 01:24:06,123
It's been five years.

1181
01:24:06,249 --> 01:24:11,248
I've just agreed to defend
that man in Draguignan.

1182
01:24:11,416 --> 01:24:13,415
He murdered his child.

1183
01:24:13,583 --> 01:24:16,665
He beat his 3-year-old son to death.

1184
01:24:18,249 --> 01:24:21,707
I may be crazy, but I've decided
to take on his case.

1185
01:24:24,208 --> 01:24:27,582
I think I won't wait for Sabine.

1186
01:24:28,374 --> 01:24:30,582
Why should I worry about Antoine

1187
01:24:30,749 --> 01:24:33,248
when my own life is so confused?

1188
01:24:34,666 --> 01:24:37,498
The things lawyers have to do!

1189
01:24:38,791 --> 01:24:40,957
I love a man. He runs a bookshop.

1190
01:24:41,124 --> 01:24:42,707
I love Sabine's brother.

1191
01:24:42,874 --> 01:24:45,957
I must tell him I love him before it's too late.

1192
01:24:46,333 --> 01:24:48,207
I can't waste time. Wait!

1193
01:24:48,374 --> 01:24:51,207
Take this. It's a picture of Sabine.

1194
01:24:51,416 --> 01:24:55,123
If Antoine gets it back, I can't explain it all,

1195
01:24:55,291 --> 01:24:57,707
but it may lead to a happy ending.

1196
01:25:09,499 --> 01:25:11,332
A letter for your pal.

1197
01:25:21,791 --> 01:25:23,707
Wake up. It's 7 a.m.

1198
01:25:23,874 --> 01:25:25,957
This came for you.

1199
01:26:56,999 --> 01:26:59,123
I made love to you right away.

1200
01:26:59,291 --> 01:27:01,498
I wanted to as much as you did.

1201
01:27:01,749 --> 01:27:05,373
Later on, I asked you where we stood.

1202
01:27:06,166 --> 01:27:08,498
You wouldn't answer my question.

1203
01:27:09,041 --> 01:27:11,248
I decided to protect myself.

1204
01:27:12,416 --> 01:27:14,457
I don't know much,

1205
01:27:14,624 --> 01:27:16,457
but I'm sure that two people
who love each other

1206
01:27:16,624 --> 01:27:18,165
should share everything.

1207
01:27:18,333 --> 01:27:22,582
What happens to one,
happens to both without exceptions.

1208
01:27:23,249 --> 01:27:25,665
If I'm wrong, I don't understand love.

1209
01:27:28,499 --> 01:27:30,957
I knew what I expected of you.

1210
01:27:31,124 --> 01:27:33,165
When I realised you couldn't decide

1211
01:27:33,333 --> 01:27:36,207
between life with me, or without me.

1212
01:27:36,874 --> 01:27:39,082
I knew I had to be careful.

1213
01:27:41,249 --> 01:27:44,290
I did my best to control my feelings for you.

1214
01:27:45,583 --> 01:27:46,998
I failed.

1215
01:27:47,166 --> 01:27:51,123
Since I hate suffering,
I decided to stop seeing you.

1216
01:27:52,291 --> 01:27:55,082
I let you pick me up in the store. It was fun.

1217
01:27:55,416 --> 01:27:56,873
I don't regret it.

1218
01:27:57,458 --> 01:28:01,415
But in this shop,
pick-up artists are a dime a dozen.

1219
01:28:01,583 --> 01:28:03,165
How can you say that?

1220
01:28:03,749 --> 01:28:05,707
I'm not a pick-up artist.

1221
01:28:05,874 --> 01:28:08,165
Yes, you are.

1222
01:28:08,333 --> 01:28:11,082
I can spot them before they walk in

1223
01:28:11,249 --> 01:28:13,998
from the way they ogle me
through the window.

1224
01:28:14,708 --> 01:28:16,998
I came here looking for you.

1225
01:28:17,166 --> 01:28:20,248
I'd already known you for two weeks.

1226
01:28:20,416 --> 01:28:22,082
- It's not true!
- It isn't?

1227
01:28:22,166 --> 01:28:23,207
Of course not.

1228
01:28:23,291 --> 01:28:25,332
Listen to me carefully.

1229
01:28:27,624 --> 01:28:31,123
One day last year, I went into a cafe
to make a phone call.

1230
01:28:31,666 --> 01:28:34,248
The phone booth was in the basement.

1231
01:28:34,333 --> 01:28:36,665
There was a man inside.

1232
01:28:36,916 --> 01:28:38,873
He was yelling.

1233
01:28:39,249 --> 01:28:41,457
He was in rage.

1234
01:28:41,624 --> 01:28:43,082
I overheard him.

1235
01:28:43,791 --> 01:28:46,123
I gathered he was screaming at a woman,

1236
01:28:46,291 --> 01:28:47,998
breaking things off with her.

1237
01:28:48,291 --> 01:28:50,707
At one point,

1238
01:28:50,874 --> 01:28:53,457
the man became violent.

1239
01:28:53,833 --> 01:28:55,998
He took a picture out of his pocket,

1240
01:28:56,166 --> 01:28:57,998
like a postcard.

1241
01:28:58,166 --> 01:29:00,290
Wedging the phone on his shoulder,

1242
01:29:00,999 --> 01:29:02,540
he tore up the picture

1243
01:29:02,708 --> 01:29:03,707
just like that.

1244
01:29:03,874 --> 01:29:06,415
He threw the pieces to the floor.

1245
01:29:07,166 --> 01:29:09,498
After hanging up, he stormed out.

1246
01:29:10,791 --> 01:29:14,790
So I went in, into the booth.

1247
01:29:15,499 --> 01:29:18,248
I don't know why I did it,

1248
01:29:18,958 --> 01:29:21,915
but I picked up all the pieces

1249
01:29:22,583 --> 01:29:23,915
and put them in my pocket.

1250
01:29:24,249 --> 01:29:26,790
Back home, I went to work

1251
01:29:27,083 --> 01:29:30,540
and constructed the picture with scotch tape.

1252
01:29:31,708 --> 01:29:33,290
After a while,

1253
01:29:33,624 --> 01:29:35,373
as if by magic,

1254
01:29:35,541 --> 01:29:37,123
the puzzle was assembled.

1255
01:29:37,666 --> 01:29:39,790
A woman's face emerged.

1256
01:29:40,333 --> 01:29:41,332
I fell in love,

1257
01:29:41,666 --> 01:29:43,582
madly in love with her.

1258
01:29:43,916 --> 01:29:45,915
I ran to the photographer

1259
01:29:46,083 --> 01:29:48,373
whose imprint was on the picture.

1260
01:29:48,791 --> 01:29:52,707
He had sold his shop.
No one knew where he'd moved to.

1261
01:29:52,958 --> 01:29:55,082
I searched all of Paris

1262
01:29:55,249 --> 01:29:56,457
to find him.

1263
01:29:56,624 --> 01:29:57,873
I asked everyone,

1264
01:29:58,041 --> 01:29:59,498
went everywhere.

1265
01:29:59,666 --> 01:30:01,248
I bothered strangers

1266
01:30:01,416 --> 01:30:02,957
who reacted angrily.

1267
01:30:03,124 --> 01:30:04,623
Often, I had to run like hell.

1268
01:30:04,791 --> 01:30:06,498
I tailed people.

1269
01:30:07,208 --> 01:30:08,248
At long last,

1270
01:30:08,416 --> 01:30:10,832
I managed to track the woman down.

1271
01:30:11,333 --> 01:30:12,707
I learned her name.

1272
01:30:13,124 --> 01:30:15,748
In time, I found out

1273
01:30:15,916 --> 01:30:17,165
where she worked.

1274
01:30:17,333 --> 01:30:18,582
During all this time,

1275
01:30:18,749 --> 01:30:22,207
the picture of the woman
I already loved never left me.

1276
01:30:22,541 --> 01:30:23,540
Want to see it?

1277
01:30:25,499 --> 01:30:26,540
Look!

1278
01:30:30,333 --> 01:30:33,748
I remember.
You wanted a non-existent record.

1279
01:30:34,083 --> 01:30:37,457
I concealed my feelings for you.

1280
01:30:37,791 --> 01:30:39,457
I even made you laugh.

1281
01:30:39,624 --> 01:30:43,248
You came back again
and made me fall in love with you.

1282
01:30:43,666 --> 01:30:45,707
I couldn't figure you out.

1283
01:30:45,874 --> 01:30:49,040
I thought, "He hasn't even noticed I'm a girl."

1284
01:30:49,208 --> 01:30:51,873
Yet my heart was pounding away.

1285
01:30:52,041 --> 01:30:53,540
You sure fooled me.

1286
01:30:53,708 --> 01:30:55,457
If I'd known. . .

1287
01:30:55,624 --> 01:30:58,040
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

1288
01:30:58,458 --> 01:31:01,873
I've concealed my feelings all my life.

1289
01:31:02,041 --> 01:31:03,623
I've always been evasive.

1290
01:31:03,791 --> 01:31:05,832
You don't trust anyone.

1291
01:31:05,999 --> 01:31:09,123
I trust you Sabine. I really do.

1292
01:31:09,541 --> 01:31:12,248
There's no way of knowing if it will last.

1293
01:31:12,416 --> 01:31:13,748
- Why not?
- It might.

1294
01:31:13,916 --> 01:31:14,915
Let's pretend.

1295
01:31:15,083 --> 01:31:16,748
- We'll see.
- Yes, we'll see.

1296
01:31:21,291 --> 01:31:24,123
Do you have Alain Souchon's last record?

1297
01:31:24,291 --> 01:31:26,915
You're in luck. It just came in.

1298
01:31:29,499 --> 01:31:30,873
It's called Love On The Run.

1299
01:31:31,041 --> 01:31:32,248
Can we hear it?

1300
01:31:32,416 --> 01:31:33,665
In the booth.

